Message: The user completes the submission of the form

Hi there, so I noticed that my ad was rejected for the use of celebs.

However, you can see that the ad is not using a celebrity endorsement at all. It's just talking about a news event that happened to Donald Trump. 

Would that be ok? Please let me know.

Hi Jackson, I understand your concern. If you believe that your ad complies with the policies and the rejection was a misunderstanding, you can submit an appeal by emailing adsupport@newsbreak.com. Make sure to explain the situation clearly and provide any necessary details to support your case. For more information, you can refer to our article on what to do if your ad gets rejected: [My ad got rejected. What's next?](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18085960681101-My-ad-got-rejected-What-s-next).
Andrew Taylor is talking to you.

Hi Jackson, I'm responding to your earlier message regarding your ad rejection. Unfortunately, we do not allow usage of any celebrity/political figures without proper endorsement. In addition, we don't allow politics/political propaganda which would include your product. We hope that answers your questions. Thank you
